---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageIntro from "../components/PageIntro.astro";
import RelatedLinks from "../components/RelatedLinks.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ"
  description="Frequently asked questions for first-time visitors to a Kamatamare Sanuki match."
>
  <PageIntro
    eyebrow="Before matchday"
    title="Frequently Asked Questions"
    description="Short answers to common questions from international visitors attending their first match."
  />
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container container--narrow faq-list">
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Do I need to speak Japanese?</h2>
        <p>
          No. Most signs and announcements may be in Japanese, but staff can usually help with
          simple questions. Keep your ticket ready and show the screen if explaining the details
          is difficult.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Where can I buy a ticket?</h2>
        <p>
          Ticket methods, prices, and seating categories may change. Use the
          <a href="https://www.kamatamare.jp/ticket/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
            >official ticket page</a
          > for current details. Check whether your seat is reserved or unreserved.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>How do I find the latest match information?</h2>
        <p>
          Check the club's official website on the day before you travel. Look for the confirmed
          venue, kick-off time, entry schedule, transport notice, and any special stadium rules.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>How early should I arrive?</h2>
        <p>
          For a first visit, arriving well before kick-off is sensible. You will need time to
          find the correct gate and seat, and you may want to look at food or merchandise.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Can away supporters attend?</h2>
        <p>
          Yes, but some seating areas restrict which team's colours and goods may be displayed.
          Check the official ticket description and matchday rules before choosing a seat.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Is food available?</h2>
        <p>
          Food and drink are normally part of the home-match experience, but the available
          stalls vary. Bring another payment method as well as a small amount of cash.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>What should I wear?</h2>
        <p>
          Wear comfortable shoes and dress for the weather. A hat and water may help in warm
          conditions; an extra layer can be useful for evening matches. Check current rules
          before bringing large bags or containers.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="faq-item">
        <h2>Is this an official guide?</h2>
        <p>
          No. This is an independent personal fan-made guide. Official club information always
          takes priority, especially for tickets, schedules, access, and stadium rules.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedLinks
    links={[
      {
        label: "Stadium & Access",
        href: "/stadium/",
        description: "Plan your route and review the matchday checklist.",
      },
      {
        label: "About this guide",
        href: "/about/",
        description: "Read the scope and limitations of this independent guide.",
      },
    ]}
  />
</BaseLayout>
